Hi all,

Problem: The cursor position in both the GtkEntry and GtkTextView are not
properly updated after moving the cursor under program control (inserting
text).

Operating System: Windows only

PHP-Gtk2 version: Gnope 1.5.1 (php-gtk2 alpha?) date stamp: July 18, 2006

Code for GtkTextView:

<?php

$clipboard = GtkClipboard::get();

$textView = new GtkTextView();

$window = new GtkWindow();
$window->add($textView);
$window->show_all();

$startMark = $textView->get_buffer()->get_insert();
$startIter = $textView->get_buffer()->get_iter_at_mark($startMark);
$startPosition = $startIter->get_offset();

echo("Before:\nTextMark: " . $startMark . "\n" .
	  "Iter: " . $startIter . "\n" .
	  "cursor position: " . $startPosition . "\n\n");

$clipboard->set_text("test");
$textView->get_buffer()->paste_clipboard($clipboard, null, true);

$endMark = $textView->get_buffer()->get_insert();
$endIter = $textView->get_buffer()->get_iter_at_mark($endMark);
$endPosition = $endIter->get_offset();

echo("After:\nTextMark: " . $endMark . "\n" .
	  "Iter: " . $endIter . "\n" .
	  "cursor position: " . $endPosition . "\n");

gtk::main();

?>


Code for GtkEntry:

<?php

$clipboard = GtkClipboard::get();

$entry = new GtkEntry();

$window = new GtkWindow();
$window->add($entry);
$window->show_all();

$startPosition = $entry->get_position();
echo("Before:\n" .
	  "cursor position: " . $startPosition . "\n\n");

$clipboard->set_text("test");
$entry->paste_clipboard();

$endPosition = $entry->get_position();
echo("After:\n" .
	  "cursor position: " . $endPosition . "\n");

gtk::main();

?>


These two code fragments work properly with Linux and FreeBSD.

-Ron T.

