Tom,

> -    NO_STATIC_METHOD();
> +    NOT_STATIC_METHOD();
That's my fault - I didn't notice that there is actually a T in.

>      zval *buttons = NULL;
> +    zval **text, **response;
That's the µ$ compiler, it doesn't let you declare variables in the mid
of a method.

